13/10/2003
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- In an interview with Radio Free Europe on Sunday (12 October), the chair of Macedonia's anti-corruption commission urged the government to show more determination in tackling the problem of corruption.
Referring to recent press criticism of her commission, Slagjana Taseva said it is working within the legal parameters and can only provide suggestions for resolving cases.
The relevant institutions must take concrete action, she added.
Taseva also called for improved communications between the cabinet and the commission.
(MIA, A1 TV - 13/10/03)
